title: For Sale:  Glock 20SF 10MM Auto W/Normal Barrel and Extra Glock 6" Barrel
postcontent:
I'm selling a Glock 20 kit that I've been putting together for myself over the past couple of years.  I've come to realize that I'm just not a Glock person so I've decided to sell it and get something else that suits me better.

The Glock 20SF is a semi-automatic pistol in the 10MM Auto cartridge.  The SF refers to the pistol having a Slim Frame.  This simply means the grips are a little smaller (easier to hold on to).  It doesn't affect any of the other attributes of the pistol.  Glock is known for manufacturing high-quality reliable firearms that operate in any environment.

10MM Auto is a high powered cartridge, right up there towards the top of the list as far as high-powered semi-autos.  It was developed for the FBI after a big shootout in Miami in which they discovered that their 9mm semi-autos and 6 shot revolvers weren't effective against well armed bank robbers.  Afterwards the FBI implemented a new pistol that fired the 10MM Auto.  Before long they realized that many FBI agents weren't 10-8 enough to handle such a powerful round. (Perhaps pushing pencils around a desk doesn't develop much arm strength ;-)  This eventually led to the creation of the 40S&W (40 Short and Weak) which is basically the sissy child of the 10MM Auto.  The 10MM Auto is an excellent defensive round for a variety of threats including large predators, zombies, and the occasional murderous car-jacker.

Included are:

1 - Glock 20SF (G3) Pistol as I bought it brand new in December of 2009 in Box with bright Trijicon Night Sights (date is 2009) all Papers, 2 Mags, Speed Loader, Brush, and some little tool that I still haven't figured out the purpose of.  I've only practiced with the pistol 4 or 5 times and it's had a total of about 250 rounds through it.  Everything is in excellent condition.  New Price: $547.00 + $92.00 for Trijicon Night Sights (=$639.00)
http://www.budsgunshop.com/catalog/product_info.php/products_id/56858

1 - Gould and Goodrich Holster, Black in color, Goldline concealment, 3-slot pancake holster for the G20, Right handed.  I got this about a month ago, it's in excellent condition and looks quite nice.  New price: $65.00 more or less.
http://www.gouldusa.com/products/showModel.php?bare_page=1&id_option=929

1 - Extra Glock Factory 6" barrel for the G20.  Never used, never fired.  Good choice for hunting or zombie suppression.  New Price: $175
http://www.glockmeister.com/G20-6-GLOCK-Factory-Barrel/productinfo/G7557/

4 - G20 Factory 15rnd Mags.  New Price: $22.00 (x4=$88.00)
http://www.midwayusa.com/product/714785/glock-magazine-glock-20-10mm-auto-15-round-polymer-black#productTabLinkReviews

So all told I've spent about $967.00 on this kit...

I'm serious about wanting to get $750.00 out of it but I'll consider any reasonable offer.  If you're interested in buying the pistol, know this:  You will have to prove to my satisfaction that you are either a United States Citizen, or a person who is otherwise legally entitled to own a firearm in the US.  US Passport preferred.  Also, you'll have to sign a declaration stating that you have never been arrested for any crime, ever.  Alternatively you could pay to have the weapon transferred through an FFL, and then all of that will be his problem.  I reserve the right to refuse to sell to anyone for any reason or no reason at all.
